				\begin{document}$$\lambda = \frac{{\mathop {\sum }\nolimits_{j \in Y\mathop { \cup }\nolimits^ T}^{} \beta _j(t)}}{N}$$\end{document}λ=∑j∈Y∪Tβj(t)N, where N is the population size and βj(t) is the transmission rate of the jth infectious individual (symptomatic or treated) at time t, which is determined by the product of a population-wide scaling factor Φ estimated from seasonal influenza incidence data and the individual’s infectiousness at time t based on the within-host viral load model. Supplementary Section 6 addresses the assumptions and robustness of the model with respect to influenza virus type.
